WEBVTT

00:01.218 --> 00:02.263
Okay, you know what?

00:02.306 --> 00:03.525
I'm starting to lose
my patience.

00:03.568 --> 00:05.309
We got the results
of your lie-detector test.

00:05.353 --> 00:07.224
To the question
"did you move to New York City?"

00:07.268 --> 00:08.878
you answered "yes,"
which was truthful.

00:08.921 --> 00:10.619
"Did you move here
for a job?"

00:10.662 --> 00:11.924
"Yes." Also truthful.

00:11.968 --> 00:14.057
"Was the job dealing
in illegal products?"

00:14.101 --> 00:16.190
You answered "no,"
which was deceptive.

00:16.233 --> 00:19.019
So, that's what you want us for?
Selling water pills?

00:19.062 --> 00:20.020
You know what we want.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.630
I don't.

00:21.673 --> 00:24.633
Then you are an even bigger
idiot than I mistook you for.

00:24.676 --> 00:28.071
And I thought he was
a pretty big idiot.

00:28.115 --> 00:30.769
Hey! Hey!

00:30.813 --> 00:33.424
Hey, then turn your light off
if somebody's in there!

00:33.468 --> 00:35.426
God. I'm gonna be late
for SoulCycle.

00:35.470 --> 00:36.471
It's gonna be okay.

00:36.514 --> 00:38.125
It's Amanda K.

00:38.168 --> 00:40.083
She's the only one who plays
the trop deep house I like.

00:40.127 --> 00:42.216
-Then take Amanda J.'s class.
-Amanda J.?

00:42.259 --> 00:44.305
Amanda J. just plays
regular deep house.

00:44.348 --> 00:46.829
Okay.

00:49.962 --> 00:52.313
What are you doing?
Are you praying?

00:53.749 --> 00:54.967
-Hey.
-Hm?

00:55.011 --> 00:56.491
[ Laughing ]
Are you praying?
No.

00:56.534 --> 00:57.840
It looked -- It looked like
you were praying.

00:57.883 --> 00:59.407
-Why would I do that?
-I don't know.

00:59.450 --> 01:01.496
But if you weren't doing that,
what were you doing?

01:01.539 --> 01:03.933
I was just having a little faith
that a cab will come along

01:03.976 --> 01:06.109
and, uh, you know, putting
some good vibes out there.

01:06.153 --> 01:08.372
-To whom?
-To anyone who's listening.

01:08.416 --> 01:10.157
I don't know.
The universe.

01:10.200 --> 01:11.375
Nobody's listening.

01:11.419 --> 01:13.160
Okay. Sure.

01:13.203 --> 01:14.857
Ah.

01:14.900 --> 01:15.858
What?

01:15.901 --> 01:17.599
Oh, 'cause you --

01:17.642 --> 01:18.774
That was luck.

01:18.817 --> 01:20.036
All right.
Call it what you want.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.124
I'm gonna --
I'm gonna call it luck.

01:21.168 --> 01:22.517
Faith, luck --
same thing.

01:22.560 --> 01:23.909
Oh, is it
the same thing?

01:23.953 --> 01:25.476
Hold on just a second.

01:25.520 --> 01:27.217
Last I checked, wars aren't
fought in the name of luck.

01:27.261 --> 01:29.219
Okay.
Children aren't abused
because of luck.

01:29.263 --> 01:32.048
And I'm quite certain there's
no such thing as organized luck.Okay.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.223
Have fun
in Amanda J.'s class.

01:33.267 --> 01:34.442
-Yeah, it's Amanda K.
-Okay.

01:34.485 --> 01:35.704
Hey, can't you
just be appreciative

01:35.747 --> 01:37.140
of how great
our life is right now?

01:37.184 --> 01:39.055
Three months ago,
we were living in a trailer.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.622
-You know what I did?
-You got a job.

01:40.665 --> 01:42.014
Yes, I know.
But before that.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.539
-I --
-Don't you say it.

01:44.582 --> 01:46.062
I prayed.

01:46.106 --> 01:47.498
I prayed, and someone
answered that prayer.

01:47.542 --> 01:48.630
Someone's listening.

01:48.673 --> 01:50.240
Did God set you up
on LinkedIn?

01:50.284 --> 01:52.373
No, but I'm pretty sure
I'm the first person

01:52.416 --> 01:53.722
who's ever been hired by it.

01:53.765 --> 01:55.027
Okay?
That's a miracle.

01:55.071 --> 01:56.159
That's probably true.

01:57.247 --> 01:58.553
Bye.

01:58.596 --> 02:00.337
-I'm praying for you.
-Please don't.

02:04.950 --> 02:06.648
-Tits up.
-Bankrupt?

02:06.691 --> 02:08.737
Perils of having
entrepreneurial dreams

02:08.780 --> 02:10.217
in an over-regulated economy.

02:10.260 --> 02:13.220
What the hell
are you doing, son?

02:13.263 --> 02:14.395
Hm?

02:14.438 --> 02:16.092
You're not praying,
are you?

02:16.136 --> 02:17.963
I thought I hired
a thinking man,

02:18.007 --> 02:20.444
not some child who still
believes in fairy tales.

02:20.488 --> 02:21.576
Come on, grow up.

02:21.619 --> 02:24.187
♪ Somewhere behind the skyline

02:24.231 --> 02:26.755
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

