I want you to turn to the person
next to you and say, "G'day!"

11:17.111 --> 11:18.242
G'day!G'day!G'day!G'day!

11:18.286 --> 11:19.374
[ Australian accent ]
G'day!

11:19.417 --> 11:20.375
Don't.
Your accent's terrible.

11:20.418 --> 11:21.942
Yeah!

11:21.985 --> 11:24.379
Now, tell that person that
you're happy to see them.

11:24.422 --> 11:25.597
I'm happy to see you!

11:25.641 --> 11:26.511
I am glad --

11:26.555 --> 11:28.122
I'm happy to see you.

11:28.165 --> 11:29.253
Okay.

11:29.297 --> 11:30.559
I'm so happy to see you.

11:30.602 --> 11:32.256
I'm happy to see you,
Mr. Parker.

11:32.300 --> 11:33.780
Happy to see you,
Mr. Parker.

11:33.823 --> 11:35.607
Well, I'm happy
to see you guys.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.261
Even though
I already saw you.

11:37.305 --> 11:40.047
Still,
it's great to be seen again.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.526
It is, isn't it?

11:41.570 --> 11:45.748
Oh, you can feel the love!
Can you feel it?

11:45.792 --> 11:47.315
[ Audience cheers ]

11:47.358 --> 11:48.751
Can you smell it?

11:48.795 --> 11:50.535
[ Audience cheers ]

11:50.579 --> 11:52.450
All right.
Let's not get too crazy.

11:52.494 --> 11:54.975
Hey, why don't you give
that special person next to you

11:55.018 --> 11:56.672
a big ol' hug?

11:57.804 --> 11:58.979
Oh, no, no, no.
That's okay.

11:59.022 --> 12:00.154
All right.
Nothing wrong with that.

12:00.197 --> 12:02.591
Maybe even a kiss.

12:02.634 --> 12:04.071
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:04.114 --> 12:05.899
Definitely no.

12:05.942 --> 12:08.902
Oh, okay.
Nothing wrong with that.

12:08.945 --> 12:09.903
Innocent.

12:09.946 --> 12:10.947
Mnh-mnh.

12:15.169 --> 12:16.431
Ah, why not?

12:16.474 --> 12:17.780
Levi: Amen! Yeah!

12:17.824 --> 12:19.434
Made you feel left out.

12:19.477 --> 12:20.696
[ Girls giggle ]

12:20.740 --> 12:21.828
[ Clears throat ]
What?

12:21.871 --> 12:23.960
Now, folks,
I want to bring

12:24.004 --> 12:26.484
some special friends
out on the stage here.

12:26.528 --> 12:30.880
Would you please welcome
Chad, Summer, Jess,

12:30.924 --> 12:32.839
Delilah, and Jareb!

12:32.882 --> 12:33.796
What?!

12:33.840 --> 12:35.580
[ Laughs ]

12:35.624 --> 12:37.017
I thought I had more time
in the show.

12:37.060 --> 12:38.540
-I was gonna tell you.
-You are sacrificing

12:38.583 --> 12:39.933
your children
for the sake of business?

12:39.976 --> 12:42.239
-They wanted to do it.
-Oh, that is low.

12:42.283 --> 12:43.850
Look at Delilah.
Come on.

12:47.679 --> 12:48.724
Ah, great!

12:48.768 --> 12:50.421
Come on,
she's in heaven.

12:50.465 --> 12:52.641
I'm in hell.But these people
are so nice to her!

12:52.684 --> 12:54.861
Do you know who else
is nice to children?Oh, don't.

12:54.904 --> 12:56.384
Drug dealers, pedophiles.

12:56.427 --> 12:58.212
We're going.
Let's go.No. Hey, we can't.

12:58.255 --> 13:00.823
Three minutes to baptism,
folks!

13:00.867 --> 13:01.824
[ Chuckles ]

13:01.868 --> 13:03.478
It's...

13:03.521 --> 13:05.088
Come on!

13:05.132 --> 13:06.611
This church accepts gay people.
How bad can it be?

13:06.655 --> 13:07.917
I'm not gay.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.701
No, I didn't --
I didn't think you were.

13:09.745 --> 13:12.748
It's fine.
Right?

13:12.792 --> 13:14.663
Well, when he comes out,
they'll accept him.

13:14.706 --> 13:15.707
-Babe, please.
-No!

13:15.751 --> 13:17.231
-You have to!
-Why?

13:17.274 --> 13:18.841
Because if you don't,
my business will go bankrupt

13:18.885 --> 13:20.582
and we'll be living
in a trailer park.

13:20.625 --> 13:22.018
[ Applause ]

13:22.062 --> 13:24.891
Ladies and gents,
the first true step in faith

13:24.934 --> 13:28.633
is admitting that you believe
in something more than yourself,

13:28.677 --> 13:32.028
and committing before
your brothers and sisters.

13:32.072 --> 13:34.857
You've already met
Delilah and Jareb.

13:34.901 --> 13:35.945
They believe!

13:35.989 --> 13:37.294
[ Cheers and applause ]

13:37.338 --> 13:38.208
Whoo!

13:38.252 --> 13:40.863
Take a bow, kids.

13:40.907 --> 13:43.692
But their parents...

13:43.735 --> 13:47.348
well, that's another story.

13:47.391 --> 13:48.262
Oh, God.

13:48.305 --> 13:50.003
Meet Nate and Robin.

13:50.046 --> 13:51.091
Hey.

13:51.134 --> 13:54.921
That's me.
[ Chuckles ]

13:54.964 --> 13:56.618
Come on up, Nate and Robin!

13:56.661 --> 13:58.098
Please, please. please,
just do it for us,

13:58.141 --> 13:59.621
-for our family.
-Okay, okay, okay, okay!

13:59.664 --> 14:01.492
But I'm crossing
my fingers.

14:01.536 --> 14:03.016
I don't care.
Just...

14:03.059 --> 14:03.973
[ Laughing ]

14:04.017 --> 14:05.801
Thank you, everyone.
Yeah.

14:05.845 --> 14:07.063
Hi.

14:12.155 --> 14:15.245
Brothers and sisters,
I want to show you

14:15.289 --> 14:18.596
the power you can have
with a little faith.

14:18.640 --> 14:21.904
Nate, I know you like water,
a little H2O.

14:21.948 --> 14:22.862
Yeah.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.124
Why don't you take a walk?

14:24.167 --> 14:25.908
What, you want me
to jump in the pool?

14:25.952 --> 14:28.780
Well, you told me that you
believe in the power of water.

14:28.824 --> 14:29.999
I do.

14:30.043 --> 14:31.131
Well, then, take a walk.

14:31.174 --> 14:32.523
Jump.
Yeah, okay.

14:32.567 --> 14:34.351
Can you hold
my cellphone?

14:34.395 --> 14:36.527
Have a little faith, Nate.

14:36.571 --> 14:38.138
[ Cheers and applause ]

14:39.879 --> 14:41.054
All right. I do.

14:41.097 --> 14:42.359
[ Clears throat ]

14:42.403 --> 14:44.753
I guess I got to buy
a new cellphone.

14:44.796 --> 14:45.841
You can do it, Dad.

14:47.495 --> 14:50.367
Oh, God,
I hope this water's warm.

14:53.327 --> 14:54.371
Oh, shit!

14:54.415 --> 14:55.372
Oh, shit!

14:55.416 --> 14:56.852
Holy shit!

14:56.896 --> 14:58.506
-I'm sorry to swear, but --
-It's okay, Nate.

14:58.549 --> 15:01.422
God created curse words
for moments just like this.

15:01.465 --> 15:03.641
The moment you believed
He was real.

15:03.685 --> 15:06.557
Holy shit!
Jesus Christ!

15:06.601 --> 15:08.081
-Okay, settle down.
-Yeah, sorry.

15:08.124 --> 15:09.430
Nate, come on.
It's a trick.

15:09.473 --> 15:10.866
It's not a trick, Mom!

15:10.910 --> 15:12.085
You think your father
can walk on water?

15:12.128 --> 15:13.956
I'm walking on water!

15:14.000 --> 15:16.916
[ Cheers and applause ]

15:16.959 --> 15:18.395
People can't walk
on water.

15:18.439 --> 15:19.701
I want to have faith, Mom.
I want to believe!

15:19.744 --> 15:21.224
Yeah, so we can do
stuff like this.

15:21.268 --> 15:23.052
It's a table, guys.
I can see it.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.272
-I can't see anything.
-Just keep on walking, Nate.

15:25.315 --> 15:26.969
-[ Laughs ]
-Hey, it's like in Vegas,

15:27.013 --> 15:29.276
the thing that we put
our beer on at the swim-up bar?

15:29.319 --> 15:31.931
In Vegas, I can't do this.
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

15:31.974 --> 15:34.411
I'm dancing on water!
Whoo-hoo!

15:34.455 --> 15:35.891
I'm dancing.

15:35.935 --> 15:38.415
Oh, my God.
This is such a stupid trick.

15:38.459 --> 15:40.287
If you're so sure, Robin,
give it a try.

15:40.330 --> 15:41.505
You got to try this, babe.

15:41.549 --> 15:42.332
Okay.

15:42.376 --> 15:43.855
It's awesome.

15:43.899 --> 15:44.769
Oh, shoot!

15:44.813 --> 15:46.249
It was here.
It was here.

15:46.293 --> 15:47.424
It was right here.

15:47.468 --> 15:49.122
It was right --
right here.

15:49.165 --> 15:50.514
It was right here!

15:50.558 --> 15:52.342
Babe, just get out.
Come on, come on.

15:52.386 --> 15:53.909
You still think
it's a trick?

15:53.953 --> 15:56.042
I obviously --
I didn't step where he stepped.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.478
I think you did,
actually.

15:57.521 --> 15:59.088
Nate, do you think
it's a trick?

15:59.132 --> 16:01.395
Uh...
I don't know.

16:01.438 --> 16:02.439
Faith, Nate!

16:02.483 --> 16:03.745
I...

16:03.788 --> 16:05.399
Then, no,
I don't think it's a trick.

16:05.442 --> 16:09.011
Yes! Yes, it is!
Look!

16:09.055 --> 16:10.447
[ Laughter ]

16:10.491 --> 16:12.406
Stop laughing at me,
you misfits!

16:12.449 --> 16:13.798
It's a goddamn trick!

16:13.842 --> 16:14.974
[ Audience booing ]

16:15.017 --> 16:17.237
Oh, don't --
don't boo me.

16:17.280 --> 16:20.153
Use your heads.
This guy is a fraud.

16:20.196 --> 16:21.850
You're following
a magician

16:21.893 --> 16:23.765
who forced his wife
to marry him.

16:23.808 --> 16:25.985
Who said forced?
I said it was arranged.

16:26.028 --> 16:27.421
Oh, whatever.

16:27.464 --> 16:29.205
Marriage under Draconian
measures. Same thing.

16:29.249 --> 16:31.077
Well, statistically,
arranged marriages

16:31.120 --> 16:32.774
are the most successful
marriages.

16:32.817 --> 16:35.037
Well, statistically most
of the people in this room

16:35.081 --> 16:36.865
have herpes,
so don't throw stats at me.

16:36.908 --> 16:38.214
I don't think that's true.

16:38.258 --> 16:39.694
Robing: And you want to know
another thing?

16:39.737 --> 16:41.087
This dingo...

16:41.130 --> 16:42.566
Yeah, that's right.

16:42.610 --> 16:45.352
I compared him to a dog
that eats babies.

16:45.395 --> 16:49.051
This dingo is flying around
the world in his private jet

16:49.095 --> 16:51.401
while you're throwing
your hard-earned cash at him.

16:51.445 --> 16:53.055
Everyone here knows
about my jet.

16:53.099 --> 16:54.709
Everyone here
is proud of my jet.

16:54.752 --> 16:56.058
Right?

16:56.102 --> 16:59.279
Audience: J-E-T, yes!
Jet! Jet! Jet!

16:59.322 --> 17:02.108
[ Cheers and applause ]

17:03.674 --> 17:06.808
How else would I deliver
basic supplements and vitamins

17:06.851 --> 17:08.157
to third-world nations?

17:08.201 --> 17:09.376
Commercial flights?

17:09.419 --> 17:12.335
[ Laughter ]

17:12.379 --> 17:13.380
Okay, okay.

17:13.423 --> 17:14.729
Did you know
that right now

17:14.772 --> 17:16.731
he is doing a deal
with my husband

17:16.774 --> 17:19.690
to get some "supplements"
that are basically just water?

17:19.734 --> 17:20.778
What are you doing?

17:20.822 --> 17:21.953
I am proving a point.

17:21.997 --> 17:22.867
A terrible one.

17:22.911 --> 17:24.260
It is true, folks.

17:24.304 --> 17:26.349
I am in a business deal
with Nate here.

17:26.393 --> 17:27.916
But that's because I think

17:27.959 --> 17:30.136
God put Nate in my life
for a reason.

17:30.179 --> 17:32.355
I recently prayed
that I would meet someone

17:32.399 --> 17:34.444
that would help supplement
my teachings.

17:34.488 --> 17:36.359
And on the very same day,

17:36.403 --> 17:39.841
an actual supplement salesman
cold-called me.

17:39.884 --> 17:43.410
Now, are the pills that
he's selling black mamba oil?God, no.

17:43.453 --> 17:46.326
Or are they simply
a reminder to hydrate?You bet.

17:46.369 --> 17:50.199
I mean, water is the most
important element on Earth!

17:50.243 --> 17:52.680
All life needs it
to flourish!

17:52.723 --> 17:55.726
It's what separates us
from Mars!

17:55.770 --> 17:57.250
[ Cheers and applause ]

17:57.293 --> 17:59.078
I said that.
That's my quote.

17:59.121 --> 18:00.383
It's on the pamphlet.

18:00.427 --> 18:02.994
I accept Jesus
as my lord and savior!

18:03.038 --> 18:04.387
Whoa!

18:04.431 --> 18:06.911
Jesus lets us swear!

18:06.955 --> 18:08.130
Shit snacks!

18:08.174 --> 18:09.523
Nate: Oh, geez.
Really?

18:09.566 --> 18:12.003
Looks like we're in business
together, Nate.

18:12.047 --> 18:13.744
Let's call it
200,000 units.

18:13.788 --> 18:16.095
Uh, okay then.

18:16.138 --> 18:17.574
Look, I know
you feel foolish.

18:17.618 --> 18:19.098
But, baby,
he saved us, okay?

18:19.141 --> 18:20.969
Oh, geez!

18:21.012 --> 18:22.710
♪ It's Bible 2.0

18:22.753 --> 18:25.669
♪ Everyone is welcome,
all your friends and foes ♪

18:25.713 --> 18:27.410
♪ Bring all the Jews

18:27.454 --> 18:29.456
♪ And the black
and the rainbow ♪

18:29.499 --> 18:33.721
♪ Everyone is welcome,
all your friends and foes ♪

18:33.764 --> 18:35.157
♪ You are a shaman,
I say amen ♪

18:35.201 --> 18:36.637
♪ We be jammin' with Jah

18:36.680 --> 18:38.465
♪ We all just players
in this game ♪

18:38.508 --> 18:40.380
♪ So don't throw shade
on Allah ♪

18:40.423 --> 18:42.469
♪ You got the spot
upon your forehead ♪

18:42.512 --> 18:44.340
♪ Or your Lord isn't white

18:44.384 --> 18:48.301
We're saved!
We're saved!

18:48.344 --> 18:49.737
Whoo!

18:54.350 --> 18:55.960
And I'm literally
standing on the water.

18:56.004 --> 18:57.223
-What?
-Yeah, I don't know.

18:57.266 --> 18:58.615
Some Plexiglas trick
or something.

18:58.659 --> 19:00.226
Anyway, the guy's like,

19:00.269 --> 19:01.705
[Australian accent] "I'll take
200,000 units of those."

19:01.749 --> 19:03.011
[ Normal voice ]
And I'm like,

19:03.054 --> 19:04.491
"I don't even know
what a unit is."

19:04.534 --> 19:06.014
But somebody
just saved the company!

19:06.057 --> 19:08.364
[ Laughs ]

19:10.932 --> 19:12.977
[ Bird cawing ]

19:13.021 --> 19:15.284
Did we get off
on the right floor?

19:17.852 --> 19:20.550
What the hell
is going on here?

19:20.594 --> 19:22.465
What did you do to us?

19:22.509 --> 19:25.033
What do you mean me?
I didn't do anything.

19:25.076 --> 19:27.253
I have no idea
what's going on here.

19:27.296 --> 19:29.646
-You're the boss!
-What do I do now?

19:29.690 --> 19:33.433
-I moved from Syracuse for this.
-I quit my last job for this.

19:33.476 --> 19:34.825
Who's the boss here?

19:34.869 --> 19:36.218
He is!He is!He is!He is!

19:36.262 --> 19:38.873
We don't have any power!
For real this time!

19:38.916 --> 19:40.309
I'm not the boss!

19:40.353 --> 19:43.486
♪♪

19:57.500 --> 20:00.199
I just need you to know
that I really hate liars.

20:00.242 --> 20:02.331
My dad's pathological,
and I hate my dad.

20:02.375 --> 20:03.811
My father deals
on the black market.

20:03.854 --> 20:04.986
That's all you
need to know.

20:05.029 --> 20:06.379
Bag's gone.My dad.

20:06.422 --> 20:08.555
My father gave me it
before he walked out on us.

20:08.598 --> 20:11.035
Edie: I repeat, abort!
We have bigger fish to fry.

20:11.079 --> 20:13.603
We're not even remotely close
to finding the Big Tuna.

20:13.647 --> 20:15.170
-Big Tuna!
-Goddamn Big Tuna!

20:15.214 --> 20:16.737
-What about Dad?
-Where's your dad?

20:16.780 --> 20:18.347
-He went to get my mom.
-Can't wait to see her.

20:18.391 --> 20:19.827
Our piece-of-shit dad
walked out on her.

20:19.870 --> 20:22.438
[ Conversing in Cantonese ]

20:24.745 --> 20:27.313
[ Speaking Cantonese ]

20:27.356 --> 20:28.836
[ Clicking tongue ]

20:28.879 --> 20:30.359
Did God set you up
on LinkedIn?

20:30.403 --> 20:32.187
No, but I'm pretty sure
I'm the first person

20:32.231 --> 20:33.275
who's ever been hired by it.

20:33.319 --> 20:34.755
Okay?
That's a miracle.

20:34.798 --> 20:36.757
[ Echoing ]
I call it the Robin's Nest.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.628
-That's my wife's name.
-Must be a sign!

20:40.064 --> 20:45.287
Hey, there, Gummy Bear.

20:45.331 --> 20:47.028
Daddy's back.

20:49.117 --> 20:50.814
Holy shit.

20:50.858 --> 20:52.294
What?

20:52.338 --> 20:55.210
I have no idea
what happened here.

20:55.254 --> 20:58.387
I really don't.

20:58.431 --> 20:59.649
Like, not a clue.
